      <!-- ===========================
           MISSION SECTION
           =========================== -->
      <h2 class="section-title">Our Mission</h2>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>

      <div class="info-containers default-font">
        <p>Our mission with this research project is to provide resources and opportunities to those who seek adaptive clothes. Finding reliable information on available brands and leading research can be difficult at times. The main goal of this website is to compile all of the information gathered throughout the terms and condense the information into one palatable source.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- ===========================
           ABOUT US SECTION
           =========================== -->
      <h2 class="section-title">About Us</h2>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>

      <div class="info-containers default-font">
        <p>We are a team of Oregon State University students in the Design for Social Impact program (DSI). This team aims to understand barriers in mainstream fashion and co-create solutions with disabled community members. Our work focuses on inclusive design principles, clear product information, and accessibility-first navigation.</p>

        <!-- Link to OSU DSI website -->
        <a href="https://dsi.oregonstate.edu/" target="_blank">
          Learn more about the DSI program here!
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- ===========================
           PROJECT SPONSOR SECTION
           =========================== -->
      <h2 class="section-title">Project Sponsor</h2>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>

      <div class="info-containers default-font">

        <!-- Sponsor image -->
        <img src ="https://bolanledahunsi.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Dahunsi_Profile-1024x1012.jpg" 
             alt="Bolanle Dahunsi" />

        <p>Bolanle Dahunsi is an Assistant Professor in the College of Business at Oregon State University. She teaches courses in Digital Design for Apparel and Apparel Design with Draping. She hopes to help her students learn to make informed design decisions that balance aesthetics, functionality, accessibility, and sustainability.</p>

        <!-- Link to sponsor website -->
        <a href="https://bolanledahunsi.com/" target="_blank">
          Learn more about Bolanle Dahunsi here!
        </a>
      </div>

